 "cells": [

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7b015650-ecdd-4346-834b-034e78ae9e00",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Twiss"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c5929fe4-eb4a-44c4-8a50-1164ef5f5d80",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This is an example of plotting lines and twiss results.\n",
    "First, create a simple line and a tracker:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "5dcde2bb-196e-4872-a5da-0881e7bfd2f2",
   "metadata": {
    "mystnb": {
     "code_prompt_show": "Show imports"
    },
    "tags": [
     "hide-cell",
     "remove-output"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%load_ext autoreload\n",
    "%autoreload 2\n",
    "\n",
    "import xtrack as xt\n",
    "import xpart as xp\n",
    "import xplt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "xplt.apply_style()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "2b066eaf-bdc5-490d-b44d-7691a0c1d85c",
   "metadata": {
    "mystnb": {
     "code_prompt_show": "Show line generation code"
    },
    "tags": [
     "remove-output",
     "hide-cell"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Found suitable prebuilt kernel `default_only_xtrack`.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "## Generate a simple 6-fold symmetric FODO lattice\n",
    "\n",
    "n = 6  # number of sections\n",
    "elements = {\n",
    "    \"QF\": xt.Multipole(length=0.3, knl=[0, +0.63]),\n",
    "    \"QD\": xt.Multipole(length=0.3, knl=[0, -0.48]),\n",
    "    \"MU\": xt.Multipole(length=0.5, knl=[np.pi / n], hxl=[np.pi / n]),\n",
    "}\n",
    "parts = {\n",
    "    \"a\": [xt.Node(0.7, \"QF\"), xt.Node(1.4, \"MU\"), xt.Node(2.1, \"QD\"), xt.Node(2.8, \"MU\")],\n",
    "    \"b\": [xt.Node(2.2, \"MU\"), xt.Node(2.9, \"QD\"), xt.Node(3.6, \"MU\"), xt.Node(4.3, \"QF\")],\n",
    "}\n",
    "nodes = [xt.Node(5.0 * i, \"a\" if i % 2 else \"b\", name=f\"S{i+1}\") for i in range(n)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# sextupoles\n",
    "for i in range(n):\n",
    "    sx = xt.Multipole(length=0.2, knl=[0, 0, 0.5 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * (i / n))])\n",
    "    nodes.append(xt.Node(0.2, sx, from_=f\"S{i+1}\", name=f\"S{i+1}SX\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "line = xt.Line.from_sequence(\n",
    "    nodes, length=5.0 * n, sequences=parts, elements=elements, auto_reorder=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "line.particle_ref = xp.Particles()\n",
    "line.build_tracker();"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "48934877-c9bb-4ece-8327-3ba956544611",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Then determine it's twiss parameters. We use the `at_s` parameter to get the result as function of s rather than at each element only."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "e03b8a81-e4e7-47bf-87a6-f15721a8473f",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "remove-output"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Found suitable prebuilt kernel `only_xtrack_frozen_energy`.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "tw = line.twiss(method=\"4d\", at_s=np.linspace(0, line.get_length(), 500, endpoint=False))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9bf582c7-be6f-40b0-afa2-7cecc617a8e6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Default twiss plot"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "714252cd-9c38-4574-844a-ee10a3e09235",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Create a default {class}`TwissPlot <xplt.twiss.TwissPlot>`:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "19f73b0b-b2c0-40f3-9d7d-dc4d9b068f0b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.TwissPlot(tw, line=line)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6c12848a-3156-4b43-8019-23a5916c56ae",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Customisation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ace4bf8c-3038-47d3-a6b6-b174726a2008",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Use the parameter `kind` to specify what is plotted. See {class}`TwissPlot <xplt.twiss.TwissPlot>` for details."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "5136995e-7911-45a1-af25-3bcdd43bb48f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "alfx, alfy, beta0, betx, betx1, betx2, bety, bety1, bety2, betz0, c_minus, c_r1_avg, c_r2_avg, circumference, delta, dmux, dmuy, dpx, dpy, dqx, dqy, dx, dx_zeta, dy, dy_zeta, dzeta, gamma0, gamx, gamy, line_config, method, momentum_compaction_factor, mux, muy, muzeta, name, nux, nuy, nuzeta, only_markers, orientation, p0c, particle_on_co, ptau, px, py, qs, qx, qy, R_matrix, radiation_method, reference_frame, s, slip_factor, steps_r_matrix, T_rev0, values_at, W_matrix, x, y, zeta\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(\", \".join(sorted(tw.keys(), key=lambda a: a.lower())))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1b7fe7a2-cccf-4d45-9f26-1d7860c1d280",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "```{tip}\n",
    "Use prefix notation as shorthand to plot both x- and y-properties, e.g. `bet` for `betx+bety`\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "8a4aed7a-5550-4966-a35c-57cb005c1343",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x500 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.TwissPlot(tw, figsize=(6, 5), kind=\"bet,mux+muy,dx\", display_units=dict(d=\"dm\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "# show legends\n",
    "plot.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "# add some annotations\n",
    "plot.axline(\"s\", line.get_s_position(\"S6QF\"), annotation=\"My marker\", annotation_loc=\"upper\")\n",
    "plot.axspan(\"s\", 9, 11, label=\"Section\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# adjust some axes\n",
    "plot.axis(0).set(title=\"Twiss plot example\", ylim=(0, 14))\n",
    "\n",
    "# adjust line layout\n",
    "plot.artist(\"mux\").set(ls=\"--\")\n",
    "plot.artist(subplot=2).set(c=\"pet2\")\n",
    "plot.legend(2, loc=\"lower center\")  # reflect update in legend"
   ]
  },
